(3843, 256, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subcontent_0', '<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">#wardrobe #clothes #dressingroom #furniture #style #cosiness #interior #design #architecture #spacefilling</span></p>\r\n<p>Everyone has at least once dreamt of walking in the closet, like in movies. If you would want to step aside and think over your decision what to wear, if you like having everything in its place, then walk-in closets are just for you. The only disadvantage of such walk- in closets is that they occupy a considerable space in your home. In order for the room to be perfectly functional, it is important to organise all zones: upper hard-to- reach shelfs are used to keep suitcases and boxes, railings for shirts and jackets are placed just under, then comes the department for trousers and boxes for underwear, and at the bottom come shoes. Remember that preferred and often- worn clothes should be at eye level. Off-size pieces – long dresses, high boots, and overcoats – should find their place in your wardrobe, too.</p>'),
