(4468, 637, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subcontent_0', '<p style="text-align: center;">#modern classic #classic #light #white #beige #furniture #style #unusual #interior #design #architecture # ZANOTTA # MMlampadari #spacefilling</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">In order for the interior to be harmonious, it is useful to organise the elements of space. Walls and ceilings are central in the classical interiors as their panels, mouldings and frescoes bear the stamp of history. The walls are most often neutral-coloured – white, beige or grey – as they are a background for modern furniture and accessories. The colours may be introduced by ways of textile, rugs, paintings and other decoration elements.</span></p>'),
(4469, 637, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subtitle_1', ''),
