(5034, 708, '_designs_block_block-_crb_row_images_sources_2_link-_crb_image_link_0', 'homedesigning.tumblr.com'),
(5035, 708, '_designs_block_block-_crb_row_images_sources_2_link-_crb_image_link_1', 'madebylemon.co.za'),
(5036, 708, '_designs_block_block-_crb_row_images_sources_2_link-_crb_image_link_2', 'thatkindofwoman.tumblr.com'),
(5037, 708, '_designs_block_block-_crb_row_images_sources_2_link-_crb_image_link_3', 'www.shopstyle.com'),
(5038, 708, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subcontent_2', '<p style="text-align: center;">#workspace #office # workroom #workplace #furniture #style #green #girl #plant #interior #design #architecture #spacefilling</p>\r\n<p>To create an interior corresponding to your professional activity, the choice of furniture and its location are crucial. Pay special attention to the working table. Its shape, size and place in the space considerably influence the person using it. A round table creates an informal friendly atmosphere. A semi-round table suits to those who do creative work, as it creates a favourable psychological atmosphere. A square or a rectangular table symbolises strength and reliability.</p>\r\n<p>Also important is the material of which furniture is made. Using glass, you can add lightness to the space, give freedom to the creative ideas and initiatives. And, on the opposite, using wooden or monochrome textures, you will form a functional and maximally “solid” interior, which gives a feeling of robustness, strength and reliability.</p>'),
(5039, 708, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subtitle_3', ''),
(5040, 708, '_designs_block_block-_crb_row_images_3_image-_crb_d_image_0', '712'),
