(5131, 723, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subcontent_1', '<p style="text-align: center;"># kitchen #colour #brown #beige #furniture #style #children #food #fashion #interior #design #architecture # Pedini #spacefilling</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">An important detail of the kitchen, upon which you will have to decide, is a backsplash (finishing of the back wall in the kitchen). Whether you make it unobtrusive and have it bear the same colour as the kitchen furniture, or you will make it one of the central design elements, it is up to you. Aside from traditional tiles, paint, stainless steel, there is a range of interesting solutions to finish this wall. It can be marble: this material is easy for everyday use, has a unique pattern and is capable of changing any kitchen. A metallic stainless steel tile will help you achieve a modern contrast with wooden or monochrome kitchen cupboards. A simple, but nonetheless interesting solution – a slate board – is practical for kitchen, as you can always take note of a recipe on it, make a family reminder, or just place on it a nice drawing of your child.</p>'),
