(5144, 723, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subcontent_3', '<p style="text-align: center;">#kitchen #colour #green #white #furniture #style #food #interior #design #architecture # Muuto # HSkjalmp #spacefilling</p>\r\n<p>When we start cooking, questions of colour, materials and textures of our kitchen move to the background, while the organisation of the space, comfort, technological features, and an easy access to all necessary things become the most important factor. Remember the rule of an ‘equilateral triangle’ : according to the laws of ergonomics, the most important elements in the kitchen are the sink, the fridge and the cooktop. The person, who cooks, constantly moves between these three elements, which is why it is important to reduce these distances to a minimum, however, leaving the space for cutting and preparation of ingredients. The most convenient way to do is to put them in a triangle. This is the basis for the space planning in the kitchen: it can be straight, angular, or parallel. The most efficient kitchen organisation is an island: it helps not only to organise the space and complies with the rule of a triangle, but is also accessible from every side. This is particularly convenient if there are several persons working in the kitchen.</p>\r\n<p>All appliances are built in cupboards, kitchen hoods and sinks are built in working surfaces, which liberates the space, eases the care and gives freedom to create.</p>'),
