(5290, 731, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subcontent_0', '<p style="text-align: center;">#colour #mustard #brown # livingroom #furniture #style # autumn #cosiness #interior #design #architecture #spacefilling</p>\r\n<p>Mustard colour in the kitchen.</p>\r\n<p>Already the very name of the colour makes us think of food. Using warm shades of this colour in the kitchen will stimulate the appetite, simultaneously adding some cosiness. Complementary to the mustard colour as the main colour, the olive, beige and grey will look great, whereas the furniture should better be of dark shades, for example, chestnut or white – in order to add some freshness.</p>'),
