(5378, 754, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subcontent_0', '<p style="text-align: center;">#wardrobe # clothes #dressingroom #furniture #style #cosiness #interior #design #architecture #spacefilling</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Everyone has at least once dreamt of walking in the closet, like in movies. If you would want to step aside and think over your decision what to wear, if you like having everything in its place, then walk-in closets are just for you. The only disadvantage of such walk-in closets is that they occupy a considerable space in your home. In order for the room to be perfectly functional, it is important to organise all zones: upper hard-to-reach shelfs are used to keep suitcases and boxes, railings for shirts and jackets are placed just under, then comes the department for trousers and boxes for underwear, and at the bottom come shoes. Remember that preferred and often-worn clothes should be at eye level. Off-size pieces – long dresses, high boots, and overcoats – should find their place in your wardrobe, too.</p>'),
(5379, 754, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subtitle_1', ''),
(5380, 754, '_designs_block_block-_crb_row_images_1_image-_crb_d_image_0', '755'),
(5381, 754, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subcontent_1', '<p style="text-align: center;">#wardrobe # clothes #dressingroom #furniture #style #cosiness #interior #design #architecture #spacefilling #space-filling</p>\r\n<p>If you are not sure whether to have a whole room as your wardrobe, « open » wardrobes are exactly what you need. Separated by glass panels, such wardrobes will become part of your room, but at the same time they will perform their function. The advantage of such an organisation is that all clothes are always before your eyes, and the wardrobe gets enough natural light.</p>\r\n<p>You have a fantastic sense of fashion or an impressive shoe collection ? Why not make it the jewel of your room ?!</p>'),
(5382, 754, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subtitle_2', ''),
(5383, 754, '_designs_block_block-_crb_row_images_2_image-_crb_d_image_0', '756'),
(5384, 754, '_designs_block_block-_crb_row_images_sources_2_link-_crb_image_link_0', 'www.lemamobili.com'),
(5385, 754, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subcontent_2', '<p style="text-align: center;">#wardrobe # clothes #dressingroom #furniture #style #cosiness #interior #design #architecture #LemaMobili #spacefilling</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">If you however do not have enough space for such an ambitious wardrobe, do not become discouraged. Even an ordinary closet can be handy and practical, just find a good place for it in your room. For the closet not to look cumbersome, it is better to build it into the walls, to equip it with doors from floor to ceiling, and to choose a neutral finishing. It may serve not only to keep clothes, but also as a separation wall dividing the space into zones.</p>'),
