(5409, 761, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subcontent_0', '<p style="text-align: center;">#colour #dustypink #soft #livingroom #furniture #style #fashion #girl #cosiness #interior #design #architecture #spacefilling</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">If the color seems to be the right one for you, but you just want to give it a try at first, slowly but surely add it to your place with little things. Textile elements: curtains, bedding, pillows; a picture, a chair or an armchair – all those small fashionable details with a touch of the color. You might as well go further and paint the door or the cupboard pink; all of these will help you understand your own attitude to such modern trend, and this is what really is important!</p>'),
(5410, 761, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subtitle_1', ''),
(5411, 761, '_designs_block_block-_crb_row_images_1_image-_crb_d_image_0', '763'),
(5412, 761, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subcontent_1', '<p style="text-align: center;">#colour #dustypink #soft #livingroom #furniture #style #cosiness #girl #interior #design #architecture #spacefilling</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">So, by this point you are sure that pink was made for you! What should you know about it? Pink is often used to express tenderness; therefore it can reduce levels of aggression, both, internal and external. This is a calm, deep, tender and a romantic color which would totally suit the living-room. If you add bits of gray to your ash-pink shades, that would look modern and innovative. Such color scheme does not overtop tricks and features of the space, and the colors make up for peaceful and relaxing atmosphere, perfectly supplementing each other.</p>'),
(5413, 761, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subtitle_2', ''),
(5414, 761, '_designs_block_block-_crb_row_images_2_image-_crb_d_image_0', '764'),
(5415, 761, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subcontent_2', '<p style="text-align: center;">#colour #dustypink #grey #soft #livingroom #furniture #style #cosiness #fashion #girl #interior #design #architecture #spacefilling</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Speaking of modern tendencies, gray is not the only good combination with dusty pink. Another great addition to the color is marble, especially if used as a soothing element in the trio – gray, ash-pink, and marble. This is perfect for the kitchen with the marble countertop, pink walls and gray furniture!</p>'),
(5416, 761, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subtitle_3', ''),
(5417, 761, '_designs_block_block-_crb_row_images_3_image-_crb_d_image_0', '765'),
(5418, 761, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subcontent_3', '<p style="text-align: center;">#colour #dustypink #marble #soft #kitchen #furniture #style #cosiness #fashion #girl #interior #design #architecture #spacefilling</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Metal elements which are a common part of today’s décor also shouldn’t be forgotten. Any type of metal would match with the dusty pink color, but gold should obviously become your first priority. Such element can make the color look royal and noble. Stylish accessories and neat details will make your interior look elegant and complete.</p>') ;
