(5467, 742, '_designs_block_block-_crb_row_images_sources_1_link-_crb_image_link_1', 'hm.com'),
(5468, 742, '_designs_block_block-_crb_row_images_sources_1_link-_crb_image_link_2', 'www.tidyawaytoday.co.uk'),
(5469, 742, '_designs_block_block-_crb_row_images_sources_1_link-_crb_image_link_3', 'wachabuy.com'),
(5470, 742, '_designs_block_block-_crb_row_images_sources_1_link-_crb_image_link_4', 'dearfrances.com'),
(5471, 742, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subcontent_1', '<p style="text-align: center;">#colour #green #plants #freshness #livingroom #bathroom #furniture #style #girl #cosiness #interior #design #architecture #spacefilling</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">One of the ideas for making your interior visually spectacular and at the same time comfortable for everyday life is to put up a vertical garden from lush vegetation or a vegetal wall. Your imagination will help you decide whether it will be a vegetal picture, a limited fraction of the wall or even a jungle. The result will be amazing: your home will get more air and life! Close to this wall, you will breathe easier, like in a forest or a flower meadow.</p>'),
(5472, 742, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subtitle_2', ''),
(5473, 742, '_designs_block_block-_crb_row_images_2_image-_crb_d_image_0', '741'),
(5474, 742, '_designs_block_block-_crb_row_images_sources_2_link-_crb_image_link_0', 'www.home-designing.com'),
(5475, 742, '_designs_block_block-_crb_row_images_sources_2_link-_crb_image_link_1', 'www.contemporist.com'),
(5476, 742, '_designs_block_block-_crb_row_images_sources_2_link-_crb_image_link_2', 'themossdesign.com'),
(5477, 742, '_designs_block_block-_crb_row_images_sources_2_link-_crb_image_link_3', 'www.nymag.com'),
(5478, 742, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subcontent_2', '<p style="text-align: center;">#colour #green #plants #freshness #livingroom #kitchen #furniture #style #girl #interior #design #architecture #spacefilling</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">If you decided to bring some life and air to your home, you cannot do without the ordinary vivid plants. Or the extraordinary ones. For instance, you can grow at your home miniature ecosystems, so called “string gardens” which come from the Japanese kokedama. Grown in such an original way, the plants will add a note of nature and will attract anyone’s attention.</p>'),
(5479, 742, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subtitle_3', ''),
(5480, 742, '_designs_block_block-_crb_row_images_3_image-_crb_d_image_0', '743'),
(5481, 742, '_designs_block_block-_crb_row_images_sources_3_link-_crb_image_link_0', 'bylassen.com'),
(5482, 742, '_designs_block_block-_crb_subcontent_3', '<p style="text-align: center;">#colour #green #plants #freshness #livingroom #garden #style #girl #cosiness #interior #design #architecture #spacefilling</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Despite the variety of use of the green colour and different vegetal decorations, do not forget the usual pot plants. Just use interesting pots or special boxes for your mini-garden for a note of originality. It is also important to choose the correct place for your flowers. Aside from a good lighting for the plants, it is necessary to find a harmonious place in the interior of the room. Furniture for them is also important. You may take several low tables, especially chosen for this purpose, or an unconventional shelf, or even the whole cupboard.</p>'),
