(411, 1, '2017-04-20 15:49:50', '2017-04-20 13:49:50', '<p>How can we let nature in the house? There are many simple ways, which are only attractive and effective if you live in a private house. For instance, if you just open up a small part of the façade, the nature will naturally come into your house. Our client Federico chose the ideal kitchen himself, and we had to create the interior based on its style. The part of the house where the living room and the kitchen are definitely has a unique atmosphere. Due to big glazing, one can have an amazing view on the picturesque landscape, and lights and life itself fill the space in.</p>\r\n<p>We wanted to enhance the effect of lightness and airiness even more, so we played with the contrast of different textures and colors. Let the walls speak! We didn’t eclipse them with furniture and didn’t stack a great number of wardrobes, shelves, chandeliers and coffee tables in the room! Big white couches, light framed chairs, tables on thin legs and wide dark wooden surfaces created a relaxing resort atmosphere. The game of contrasts turned out great! A combination of white walls and gray or brown wooden floors is very popular in hot countries, and it creates the sense of lightness and coolness. The feeling of freedom is the result!</p>\r\n<p>Lighting appliances also highlight the lightness of space. An elegant “Arco” floorlamp by Flos in the living room zone, spot and hanging chandeliers above the table match each other greatly. And dense curtains, just like a front, limit the space and cover it from the outside. Accessories helped to warm up the interior. Small pots with plants and vases made of natural materials complement the interior and make it look complete.</p>\r\n<p>How do you like our idea? Would you like to live in such a house?</p>', 'Frederic white', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'frederic-white__trashed', '', '', '2017-06-21 12:31:41', '2017-06-21 10:31:41', '', 0, 'https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/?post_type=sf_portfolio&#038;p=411', 0, 'sf_portfolio', '', 0),
