(416, 1, '2017-04-20 15:50:56', '2017-04-20 13:50:56', 'How can we let nature in the house? There are many simple ways, which are only attractive and effective if you live in a private house. For instance, if you just open up a small part of the façade, the nature will naturally come into your house. Our client Federico chose the ideal kitchen himself, and we had to create the interior based on its style. The part of the house where the living room and the kitchen are definitely has a unique atmosphere. Due to big glazing, one can have an amazing view on the picturesque landscape, and lights and life itself fill the space in.\n\nWe wanted to enhance the effect of lightness and airiness even more, so we played with the contrast of different textures and colors. Let the walls speak! We didn’t eclipse them with furniture and didn’t stack a great number of wardrobes, shelves, chandeliers and coffee tables in the room! Big white couches, light framed chairs, tables on thin legs and', 'Frederic white', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '411-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-04-20 15:50:56', '2017-04-20 13:50:56', '', 411, 'https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/411-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(417, 1, '2017-04-20 16:00:27', '2017-04-20 14:00:27', 'A “cozy house” is a very broad term. Everyone has his own opinion on how it should look like. Someone sees it is a huge cottage house with royal columns and velvet; somebody else cannot live without a fireplace, while someone likes living surrounded with metal and glass. Doesn’t matter what “coziness” means to you, it’s always very important to want to come back home! And that’s what Bernard and Evette, doctors and our new characters think! They really wanted to have a special place where they’d be able to have rest and relax after a long working day, host their friends and play charades, read or cook their culinary delights.\r\n\r\nWe chose quiet pastel colors, white and beige shades that would allow for relaxing atmosphere and sincere talks; glossy white surfaces that reflect light, big wooden boards, bringing us back to nature and history and creating coziness. Light place with lots of air, warmth and a bit of freshness is accompanied with neat comfortable furniture (what could be better than such a mix?!). Vases, books, pictures in picture frames – all those small details complement the space instead of overloading it.\r\n\r\nWe did our best to satisfy our clients! And this is our most important principle!\r\n\r\nHow do you see your comfy house?', 'Stassart', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'stassart__trashed', '', '', '2017-06-21 09:44:28', '2017-06-21 07:44:28', '', 0, 'https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/?post_type=sf_portfolio&#038;p=417', 0, 'sf_portfolio', '', 0),
