(430, 1, '2017-04-21 10:06:38', '2017-04-21 08:06:38', '<p align="justify"><span style="color: #0d0d0d;"><span style="font-family: Arial, serif;"><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="en-US">A small apartment isn’t a bad thing. What really is important in such projects is to fit all the necessary items densely, and to leave as much free space as possible. Besides, such functionality doesn’t have to be boring. 60 square meters for a family, consisting of 4 people. Impossible</span></span></span></span><span style="color: #0d0d0d;"><span style="font-family: Arial, serif;"><span style="font-size: large;">? – </span></span></span><span style="color: #0d0d0d;"><span style="font-family: Arial, serif;"><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="en-US">you</span></span></span></span><span style="color: #0d0d0d;"><span style="font-family: Arial, serif;"><span style="font-size: large;">’</span></span></span><span style="color: #0d0d0d;"><span style="font-family: Arial, serif;"><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="en-US">ll</span></span></span></span> <span style="color: #0d0d0d;"><span style="font-family: Arial, serif;"><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="en-US">ask</span></span></span></span><span style="color: #0d0d0d;"><span style="font-family: Arial, serif;"><span style="font-size: large;">, and we\'ll say </span></span></span><span style="color: #0d0d0d;"><span style="font-family: Arial, serif;"><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="en-US">“Not at all!”</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="color: #0d0d0d;"><span style="font-family: Arial, serif;"><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="en-US">Recently we had been working on the apartment with such interior. A cozy, compact place for a happy family: Agnes, Lans, and their charming twins, Arabel and Phillis. They are still little babies, so they don’t need anything special, therefore, there are no problems with a big amount of toys and lack of space for their storage.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-646 size-full" src="https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/img_test1.png" alt="" width="1302" height="922" /></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="color: #0d0d0d;"><span style="font-family: Arial, serif;"><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="en-US">Every family is unique with its own habits and lifestyle. That’s why it’s important to think in advance what kind of renovations will be done, and what kind of furniture will be needed. Each family member should have comfortable conditions for living. A functional kitchen for Agnes, where she can experiment with the desserts; a cozy working space for Lans, where he can write his articles; and, finally, a soft place for kids, where they can watch cartoons in the future and merrily jump all around the sofa.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="color: #0d0d0d;"><span style="font-family: Arial, serif;"><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="en-US">White walls and ceiling visually enlarge the space and fill it in with light. Wooden floors are really popular nowadays due to its ability to make the space cozy and warm, and to easily match different colors and textures. A small kitchen space has everything necessary for cooking, and a marble backsplash makes the interior exquisite. Oh, what can one do when women just love marble?! Across from the kitchen we decided to place a corner sofa. By the way, Agnes is a huge fan of black and white pictures, that’s why she loves taking pictures of people and nature by herself as well. We offered her a composition of her pictures which she can change any time she likes. Combined lighting really helped us with the combination of a few functional zones. Now all the family members can do their own things with their own lighting, without interfering with each other.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="color: #0d0d0d;"><span style="font-family: Arial, serif;"><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="en-US">We tried to fill the space with light, coziness and various textures. We hope, it will be filled with the happy emotions of its owners as well! </span></span></span></span></p>', 'Merode 3', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'merode-3__trashed', '', '', '2017-06-21 09:44:28', '2017-06-21 07:44:28', '', 0, 'https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/?post_type=sf_portfolio&#038;p=430', 0, 'sf_portfolio', '', 0),
