(435, 1, '2017-04-21 10:13:42', '2017-04-21 08:13:42', '<p align="justify"><span style="color: #0d0d0d;"><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="en-US">How lucky are you? How often do you ever win anything or were in the right place at a right time and became happier? The heroes of this story gave it a try and became total winners! Recently we have organized a lottery with a prize of a free design for a winner’s apartment or house. A nice and friendly family also became the lucky one! Martha, her husband and child decided to transform their house by adding some color, style and novelty to it! What did the clients want? We definitely liked their request, because people aren’t often willing to experiment with old and new styles and colors. We can say, we’ve also won a prize, because we had to mix classics and contemporary, which definitely was an interesting task with wonderful results.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="color: #000000;"><span style="font-family: Arial, serif;"><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="en-US">Light colors definitely prevail in the interior of the house, as there are white and beige walls, curtains, and ceilings that visually expand the space and make it look lighter. Classic items of furniture and décor elements are greatly combined with the modern ones, and look even more attractive on the fair background. We left some of the very interesting elements of the old house, like the fireplace which we decorated in the classical style. The fireplace became the heart of the living room where the family loves to be.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="color: #0d0d0d;"><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="en-US">The closets and shelves are very functional and comfortable to use. Martha loved them a lot, as their family won’t have any more problems with storing children’s toys and other things which take up space!</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="color: #0d0d0d;"><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="en-US">It’s great how the problem of lack of space can be overcome quickly and without any problems, like in our case: an extra room was built upon the old part of the house where we made a little kitchen which is just enough for the family. Flowers and natural plants make the house look fresh and renovated. Succulent greens fill the house with the spirit of summer, and discreet modern compositions, abstract paintings, photos and statuettes breathe life into the interior.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="color: #0d0d0d;"><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="en-US">And are the odds ever in your favor? Don’t be afraid to take parts in lotteries, as there is nothing you can lose. Fortune favors the bold! </span></span></span></p>', 'Marta', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'marta__trashed', '', '', '2017-06-21 09:44:28', '2017-06-21 07:44:28', '', 0, 'https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/?post_type=sf_portfolio&#038;p=435', 0, 'sf_portfolio', '', 0),
