(466, 1, '2017-04-21 11:01:55', '2017-04-21 09:01:55', '<p align="justify"><span style="color: #2c2c2c;"><span style="font-family: Cambria, serif;"><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="en-US">Do you have a favorite place to go? A place where you feel comfortable, where you like literally everything from delicious meals to the interior. This interior was inspired by a visit to a restaurant. Of course, it wasn’t a random restaurant, but a favorite one. Vivienne wanted her flat to look as interesting and cozy as the interior of her favorite restaurant. Vivienne herself is a very romantic lady who loves poetry, pastel colors and luxurious textures.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="color: #2c2c2c;"><span style="font-family: Cambria, serif;"><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="en-US">The flat was brand new and almost didn’t need a redevelopment. The kitchen zone did have some constructional changes, though, and got a special kitchen counter which serves as a border between the kitchen and the living room. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="color: #2c2c2c;"><span style="font-family: Cambria, serif;"><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="en-US">We mostly worked with tender beige shades which can always be combined with black and white elements. Wooden furniture has always been popular with dreamy people, that’s why that was the first thing we offered our client. Shapes and textures of a sofa, armchairs, and curtains, and also simple abstract compositions are echoes of the favorite restaurant. We tried our best to find similar lamps, as luxurious and unusual. The space itself isn’t overloaded with small details and décor elements; it’s laconic, roomy and airy. It’s always pleasant to cook a romantic dinner in such a kitchen, and host dear guests or just read a good book.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n<p align="justify"><span style="color: #2c2c2c;"><span style="font-family: Cambria, serif;"><span style="font-size: large;"><span lang="en-US">We mixed our own approach with the client’s preferences and character, and that’s what we got… Such way of work always pays off with great results! What do you think?</span></span></span></span></p>', 'Tollenaere 4', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'tollenaere-4__trashed', '', '', '2017-06-21 09:44:28', '2017-06-21 07:44:28', '', 0, 'https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/?post_type=sf_portfolio&#038;p=466', 0, 'sf_portfolio', '', 0),
