(635, 1, '2017-06-20 15:36:03', '2017-06-20 13:36:03', '<p>Similar people attract each other… is it a judgment or a happy concourse of circumstances? For our new heroes similarity of their characters and interests works great! Joel and Avril are a sociable and merry couple, as these young people have both talent and charisma! They’ve got such a great fantasy, too! Every day they create an amazing magical world and unique characters for children books. They are the soul of any company; their home is a place not just for them but also for people from many countries. Our clients are couchserfers, that’s why they host many strangers from different parts of the world.</p>\n<p>Our clients’ apartment is located in a historical center of the city, and in spite of noise and crowds of people outside, the design has to be cozy, functional and practical. The owners need to feel comfortable, and their guests need to feel as if they are home.</p>\n<p>Concrete is a suitable material for kitchen and living room walls, as wooden floor, dark and light furniture look especially expressive on such background, which makes the space look special and neat. But why create such a wall, if our heroes already have one?! We had no doubts, so we just kept the concrete wall, accentuating the authenticity of the space and making it look original. A slate board has become another accent wall, and its multifunctionality is just amazing! Recipes of favorite meals, small drawings or notes can be written on it; and sometimes one can just leave a lovely message or words of support for their sweetheart. We combined different types of lighting that accentuate different functional zones, so one can do his job without messing with other person’s activities. Even though the place is quite small, there’s enough room for sports, arts and hosting guests.</p>\n<p>The interior is the portrait of the owners, so we tried to embody our heroes’ preferences and characteristics as much as we could. We are ready for new upcoming experiments! No struggles, just our fantasy and your wishes!</p>', 'Tollenaere 2', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '393-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-06-20 15:36:03', '2017-06-20 13:36:03', '', 393, 'https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/393-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
