(658, 26, '2017-06-21 12:43:28', '2017-06-21 10:43:28', '<p>Two-bedroom apartment, a young couple’s place where strangers get hosted</p>\r\n<p>Make-over cost : 695.64€ for the living room and kitchen (40.92m²)</p>\r\n<p>Furniture, lighting, accessories budget : 23 555€.</p>\r\n<p>Similar people attract each other… is it by accident or a happy coincidence? For our new heroes, their characters and interests work greatly together! Joel and Avril are a sociable and merry couple, young people with both charisma and unique talent! Fantasies do not hold them back! After all, every day they write amazing fairy-tales with magical worlds and unique characters for children’s books.</p>\r\n<p>This couple is the soul of any company; their home is a place not just for them but also for people from many countries. Our clients are couch-surfers, so they host strangers from all over the world.</p>\r\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-650" src="https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Tollenaere_2.jpg" alt="" width="1635" height="1402" /></p>\r\n<p>Our clients’ apartment is located in the historical center of Brussels city. In spite of the noise and crowds of people outside, the design should be cozy and practical. The owners need to feel comfortable and their guests need to feel as if they are home too.</p>\r\n<p>Concrete - a suitable material for the kitchen and living room wall finishes, contrasting nicely with the wooden floor. Dark and light furniture give the room a special atmosphere of comfort. This composition creates an impressive space. But why create such a wall, if our heroes are already impressive?! We just kept the old concrete wall to accentuate the authenticity of the space and to make it look original. A slate board has become another accent wall, and its multifunctionality is just amazing! Recipes of favorite meals, small drawings or notes can be written on it; and sometimes one can just leave a lovely message or kind words of support to your loved one. We even perfectly combined different types of lighting to accentuate certain functional areas, so one can do his job without interfering with each other. Even though the place is quite small, there’s enough room for sports, creativity and for hosting guests.</p>\r\n<p>This interior is the portrait of the owners. We tried to embody our heroes’ preferences and characteristics as much as we could. We are ready for new upcoming experiments! No complications or struggles, only our imagination and your wishes!</p>', 'Tollenaere 2', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'tollenaere-2', '', '', '2017-06-21 13:28:20', '2017-06-21 11:28:20', '', 0, 'https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/?post_type=sf_portfolio&#038;p=658', 0, 'sf_portfolio', '', 0),
(659, 26, '2017-06-21 12:54:37', '2017-06-21 10:54:37', '<p>One-bedroom apartment.</p>\r\n<p>Make-over cost : 761.09€ for the living room and kitchen (44.77m²)</p>\r\n<p>Furniture, lighting, accessories budget : 34 130.45€.</p>\r\n<p>Do you have a favorite place to go to? A place where you feel comfortable, where you like literally everything – maybe like a restaurant? from delicious meals to the interior? This interior was inspired by a visit to a restaurant. Of course, it wasn’t a random restaurant, but a favorite one, her favorite one. Vivienne wanted her flat to look as interesting and cozy as the interior of her favorite restaurant and needed to reflect herself too. She is a very romantic lady who loves poetry, pastel colors and luxurious textures.</p>\r\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-660" src="https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/tollenaere_4.png" alt="" width="1116" height="1044" /></p>\r\n<p>The flat was brand new and almost didn’t need redesign it. The kitchen zone did have some constructional changes, though, and got a special kitchen counter which serves as a border between the kitchen and the living room.</p>\r\n<p>For her interior, we mostly worked with beige shades which can always be combined with black and white elements. Wooden furniture has always been popular with dreamy people, that’s why that was the first thing we offered our client. The shapes and textures used for her sofa, armchairs and curtains, are simple abstract compositions and are the echoes of her favorite restaurant. We tried our best to find similar lamps, that look as luxurious and unusual as they have. The space itself isn’t overloaded with small details and decor elements; it’s laconic, roomy and airy. Plus, it’s always pleasant to cook a romantic dinner in such a kitchen while hosting guests or just reading a good book.</p>\r\n<p>We mixed our own approach with the client’s preferences and character. This is what we got… Working in such way always pays off with great results! What do you think?</p>', 'Tollenaere 4', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'tollenaere-4', '', '', '2017-06-21 13:28:17', '2017-06-21 11:28:17', '', 0, 'https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/?post_type=sf_portfolio&#038;p=659', 0, 'sf_portfolio', '', 0),
