(661, 26, '2017-06-21 12:57:10', '2017-06-21 10:57:10', '<p>One-bedroom apartment for a strong independent woman</p>\r\n<p>Make-over cost : 1591.03€ for the bedroom, dressing, living room and kitchen (93.59m²)</p>\r\n<p>Furniture, lighting, accessories budget : 75 504 €.</p>\r\n<p>Why is an elegance style now considered boring and dull? Maybe it’s the reason is that most people don’t take it accurately enough, because they don’t have a well-developed sense of harmony.</p>\r\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-662" src="https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Merode_1.jpg" alt="" width="1507" height="1608" /></p>\r\n<p>Elegance is a part of our client’s character. Madlen is a lawyer, and as it’s well-known from different magazines that it’s the most charismatic and most attractive woman in Hollywood; intelligent, modest and a true warrior! She is the incarnation of self-dignity, self-confidence and yet also softness. The style of this apartment has to combine all these characteristics.</p>\r\n<p>Our task was to create special coziness by combining a modern style and classical elements. Lighting, colors, materials, furniture and decorations have to match Madlen’s charm. It needs to help her relax by abling her to do her favorite things, like reading or having friends over.</p>\r\n<p>The interior includes the minimum necessary, contrasts and calmness, womanly firmness and a bit of luxury. For example, the chocolate and milk colors reminds you of rigidity and calmness. Straight and fine lines prompt stability and reliability while matching harmonically together. Dark wood and light textiles, the brown marble elements, simple geometry forms and details, make the interior soft and festive. The kitchen space is concise and modest, functional and roomy. A great place to cook and without feeling uncomfortable from lack of space or light. Kitchen, living room, bedroom and dressing room are divided with a thin see-through partition, which makes one space flow into another one, and moreover, they can be easily split up when needed. We also remembered Madlen’s wish, as a bookaholic, for her living room we created a customized library. The heroine of this story just like many other women dreamt about a spacious walk-in dressing room with a big wardrobe, with lots of hooks and shelves for all her accessories. How could we not make her dream come true?! In the bedroom, silver elements like vases, statues, and lamps make the room look exquisite and abstract monochrome paintings add bits of luxury to it.</p>\r\n<p>This is how we see elegant home coziness. Don’t settle for existing stereotypes, as the results of the experiment can be completely breathtaking!</p>', 'Merode 1', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'merode-1', '', '', '2017-06-21 13:28:44', '2017-06-21 11:28:44', '', 0, 'https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/?post_type=sf_portfolio&#038;p=661', 0, 'sf_portfolio', '', 0),
