(663, 26, '2017-06-21 12:59:02', '2017-06-21 10:59:02', '<p>Two-bedroom duplex for ambitious woman</p>\r\n<p>Make-over cost : 954.72€ for the master bedroom, living room and kitchen</p>\r\n<p>Furniture, lighting, accessories budget : 49 149€.</p>\r\n<p>Oh, how great it is when we have young romantic people, full of energy and life, coming to us!? Ah girls, these girls! Recently we have been approached by Paule, a talented stylist and make-up artist. Fashion shows, photo sessions, parties and master classes; her life is always so active! Always thousands of things to do! We had the opportunity to create a girly apartment that is cozy, luxury and fashionable. A perfect place for sleepovers and morning tea gatherings. Every woman dreams of such a place since early childhood, that’s why it was quite easy for us to understand what the client wanted.</p>\r\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-664" src="https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/merode_2.jpg" alt="" width="1645" height="1724" /></p>\r\n<p>As the amazing Christian Dior said, “Pink is tender. And gray is not boring.” And that’s exactly what we needed! The apartment is located on the attic floor and despite the small size, we managed to create a cozy place. The kitchen zone doesn’t take much space and is still big enough to cook a quick breakfast. The character of this story rarely cooks at home so this kitchen space has enough functions and comfort for her. The dining area is accentuated with a marble wall, which is a pinch of luxury and chic combined with dark and light wood textures. The interior has a lot of natural lighting, so it feels flowy and airy. Open cabinets and shelves, small poufs and tables, everything is carefully chosen to enable the owner change the furniture’s location and makes the interior look completely different. A combination of gold and dusty pink is this year’s trend and was used in our interior, like these wonderful golden hanging lamps totally go with the pink soft chairs.</p>\r\n<p>A bed is the main element of any bedroom, and ours was not the exception. A light bedroom with a big and soft bed, show an amazing view of the city through the windows. Greenery in unremarkable wireframe flower pots bring freshness and richness to all the rooms, in addition to using spotlight in the interior helps create a romantic mood.</p>\r\n<p>We are happy we managed to make young Paule’s dream come true! Dream, believe, hope and all your wishes will definitely come true!</p>', 'Merode 2', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'merode-2', '', '', '2017-06-21 13:34:00', '2017-06-21 11:34:00', '', 0, 'https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/?post_type=sf_portfolio&#038;p=663', 0, 'sf_portfolio', '', 0),
(664, 26, '2017-06-21 12:58:37', '2017-06-21 10:58:37', '', 'merode_2', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'merode_2', '', '', '2017-06-21 12:58:37', '2017-06-21 10:58:37', '', 663, 'https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/merode_2.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(665, 26, '2017-06-21 13:13:08', '2017-06-21 11:13:08', '<p>-bedroom apartment.</p>\r\n<p>Make-over cost : € for one bedroom, living and dining room (²)</p>\r\n<p>Furniture, lighting, accessories budget : €.</p>\r\n<p>How can we let nature in the house? There are many simple ways which are only attractive and effective, especially if you live in a private house. For instance, if you just open up a small part of the façade and the nature will naturally come into your home.</p>\r\n<p>Our client Federico chose the ideal kitchen himself and we had to create the interior based on its style. This part of the house, the living room and the kitchen, have definitely a unique atmosphere. Due to huge glazing, one can have an amazing view of the picturesque landscape, and lights and life itself fill the space in.</p>\r\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-692" src="https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Frederic_white.png" alt="" width="1920" height="1634" /></p>\r\n<p>We wanted to further enhance the brightness and airiness outcome, so we played with the contrast of different textures and colors. Let’s let the walls speak! We didn’t obscure them with furniture and didn’t stack a great number of wardrobes, shelves, chandeliers and coffee tables in the room! Two big white couches, light framed chairs, tables on thin legs and wide dark wooden surfaces create a relaxing atmosphere. The game of contrasts turned out great! A combination of white walls and gray with brown wooden floors is very popular in hot countries, and it creates the sense of lightness and coolness. The feeling of freedom is the result!</p>\r\n<p>Lighting appliances also highlight the space. An elegant “Arco” floorlamp by Flos in the living room zone, spots and hanging chandeliers above the table match each other greatly. Dense curtains, just like a screen, limit the space and cover it from the outside. Accessories help to warm up Frederico’s interior. Small pots with plants and vases made of natural materials perfectly complement this interior and make it look complete.</p>\r\n<p>How do you like our idea? Would you like to live in such a house?</p>', 'Frederic white', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'frederic-white', '', '', '2017-06-21 14:04:09', '2017-06-21 12:04:09', '', 0, 'https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/?post_type=sf_portfolio&#038;p=665', 0, 'sf_portfolio', '', 0),
