(668, 26, '2017-06-21 13:17:26', '2017-06-21 11:17:26', '<p>Two-bedroom duplex for a couple of doctors and their kids</p>\r\n<p>Make-over cost : 787.61€ for the living room, dining room and kitchen (46.33m²)</p>\r\n<p>Furniture, lighting, accessories budget : 24 944.50 €.</p>\r\n<p>A “cozy house” is a very broad term. Everyone has his own opinion on how it should look like. For some, it is a mansion with royal pillars and velvet, for others, they cannot imagine ‘coziness’ without a fireplace, while some even like living surrounded with metal and glass. It doesn’t matter what “coziness” means to you, however, it’s always very important to want to come back home! And that’s what Bernard and Evette, doctors and our new characters think! They really wanted to have a special place where they’d be able to relax after a long working day, host their friends and play charades, read or cook their culinary delights.</p>\r\n<p>We chose pastel colors, white and beige shades that would allow a relaxing atmosphere and sincere talks. Glossy white surfaces to reflect the light, big wooden boards that bring us back to nature and history while creating coziness. A light place with lots of air, warmth and a bit of freshness is accompanied with neat comfortable furniture (what could be better than such a mix?!). Vases, books, picture frames – all those small details complement the space instead of overloading it.</p>\r\n<p>We did our best to satisfy our clients! And this is our most important principle!</p>\r\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-694" src="https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Stassart.png" alt="" width="1920" height="1629" /></p>', 'Stassart', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'stassart', '', '', '2017-06-21 14:12:57', '2017-06-21 12:12:57', '', 0, 'https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/?post_type=sf_portfolio&#038;p=668', 0, 'sf_portfolio', '', 0),
(669, 26, '2017-06-21 13:19:10', '2017-06-21 11:19:10', '<p>Two-bedroom apartment where a young couple live.</p>\r\n<p>Make-over cost : 485.01€ for the living room, dining room and kitchen (28.53 m²)</p>\r\n<p>Furniture, lighting, accessories budget : 26 526.47 €.</p>\r\n<p>“We are young, we are free!” is the motto of our new clients, a wonderful couple, Noel and Annette. It’s amazing to work with such active, smiley and happy people!</p>\r\n<p>Usually a small living room and a kitchen is a pain in the neck… But challenge accepted! It was a chance for us to test ourselves and create a unique design for our beloved clients.</p>\r\n<p>The recipe for a happy interior in a small space is simple! We chose a great way of visually widening the space by adding fine geometrical lines and transparent partitions – who can resist those?! The favorite colors of our clients; dusty pink and dark blue, are a great match to dark surfaces of our wooden wardrobes and shelves. Plus, a combination of abstraction and everlasting classics, perky pictures and marble surfaces reflect the owner’s portrait. These two are ready to embrace all the challenges such as bold ideas and combinations. And a pinch of lush green flowers allows the freshness and coziness in the house.</p>\r\n<p>Don’t be afraid to experiment, dear friends! Even the most unreal or crazy ideas can be a new beginning of your life!</p>\r\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-670" src="https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/Stassart_2.jpg" alt="" width="1696" height="1024" /></p>', 'Stassart 2', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'stassart-2', '', '', '2017-06-21 13:31:28', '2017-06-21 11:31:28', '', 0, 'https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/?post_type=sf_portfolio&#038;p=669', 0, 'sf_portfolio', '', 0),
