(673, 26, '2017-06-21 13:22:10', '2017-06-21 11:22:10', '<p>Small two-bedroom apartment.</p>\r\n<p>Make-over cost : 494.36€ for the living room and kitchen (29.08m²)</p>\r\n<p>Furniture, lighting, accessories budget : 24 095€.</p>\r\n<p>A small apartment isn’t a bad thing. What really is important in such projects is to fit all the necessary items densely and to leave as much free space as possible. Anyways, such functionality shouldn’t be boring. We have here only 60 square meters for a family of four. Impossible? – NOT AT ALL !</p>\r\n<p>Recently we had been working on this apartment: a compact place for a happy family; Agnes, Lans and their charming twins, Arabel and Phillis. They are still little babies, so they don’t need anything special, therefore, there are no problems with having a big amount of toys nor a lack of space for their storage.</p>\r\n<p><img class="alignnone wp-image-697 size-full" src="https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/merode_3.png" alt="" width="1984" height="1403" /></p>\r\n<p>Every family is unique with its own habits and lifestyle. That’s why it’s important to think in advance what kind of renovations will be done and what kind of furniture will be needed. Each family member should have comfortable living conditions. They needed a functional kitchen for Agnes, where she can experiment with the desserts. A pleasent working space for Lans, where he can write his articles and, finally, a soft place for the kids, where they will be able to watch cartoons and merrily jump all around the sofa.</p>\r\n<p>White walls and ceiling visually enlarge the space and fill it with light. Wooden floors are really popular nowadays due to its ability to make the space cozy and warm, and thanks to easily matching colors and textures. A small kitchen space with everything necessary for cooking and a marble backsplash makes the interior exquisite. Oh, what can one do when women just love marble?! Across from the kitchen we decided to place a corner sofa. By the way, Agnes is a huge fan of black and white pictures, that’s why she loves taking pictures of people and nature. We displayed a composition of her pictures which she can change any time she likes. We also added combined lighting as it helps all the family members, they now can do their own things with their own lighting, without interfering with each other.</p>\r\n<p>We tried to fill the space with light, coziness and various textures. Now we just hope that it will also be filled with lots of happy emotions!</p>', 'Merode 3', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'merode-3', '', '', '2017-06-21 14:52:15', '2017-06-21 12:52:15', '', 0, 'https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/?post_type=sf_portfolio&#038;p=673', 0, 'sf_portfolio', '', 0),
(675, 26, '2017-06-21 13:23:28', '2017-06-21 11:23:28', '<p>Three-bedroom house for family of 3</p>\r\n<p>Make-over cost : 1868.81€ for the kitchen, dining, living, tv room, bedroom and bathroom (109.93m²)</p>\r\n<p>Furniture, lighting, accessories budget : 160 425.67€.</p>\r\n<p>How lucky are you? How often do you ever win anything or were in the right place at a right time and became happier? The heroes of this story gave it a try and became total winners! We have organized a lottery with a prize of a free design for a winner’s apartment or house. A nice and friendly family became the lucky ones! Marta, her husband and their child decided to transform their house by adding some color, style and novelty to it! We definitely liked their request, because people aren’t often willing to experiment with old and new styles nor with colors. We can say, we’ve also won a prize, because we had to mix classic and contemporary, which definitely was an interesting task and with wonderful results.</p>\r\n<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-699" src="https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/marta.png" alt="" width="3861" height="3273" /></p>\r\n<p>Light colors definitely prevail in the interior of this house, as there are white and beige walls, curtains and ceilings that visually expand the space plus make it look lighter. Classic items of furniture and décor elements are greatly combined with the modern ones, and look even more attractive on the fair background. We left some of the very interesting elements of the old house, like the fireplace which we decorated in the classical style. The fireplace became the heart of the living room where the family loves to be.</p>\r\n<p>The closets and shelves are very functional and easy to use. Marta loved them a lot, as their family won’t have any more problems with storing children’s toys and other things which take up space!</p>\r\n<p>It’s great how the problem of lack of space can be overcome quickly and without any problems, like in our case: an extra room was built where the old part of the house is, now a little kitchen has appeared. Flowers and natural plants make the house look fresh and renovated. Greenery fills the house with the summer spirit. Discreet modern compositions, abstract paintings, photos and statuettes breathe life into the interior.</p>\r\n<p>So now do you believe that the odds can be in your favor? Don’t be afraid to take part in open competitions, as there is nothing you can lose. Fortune favors the bold !</p>', 'Marta', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'marta', '', '', '2017-06-21 15:02:14', '2017-06-21 13:02:14', '', 0, 'https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/?post_type=sf_portfolio&#038;p=675', 0, 'sf_portfolio', '', 0),
(677, 26, '2017-06-21 13:24:14', '2017-06-21 11:24:14', '<p>The project is a private villa for a family consisting of 4 members: 2 adults and 2 children. This villa is located in the prestigious central part of Brussels, on a green piece of land with high walls of thick bushes and tall trees, which help to hide the house. The house is an energy-saving one, as it’s been designed in accordance with all the principles of ecological technologies. The shape of the house is oriented according to the corners of the Earth. The main idea was to make the space of the house as light and open to the sun as possible, that’s why the main northern façade is so concise and strict compared to the openness of the southern one. Thus, sunlight and warmth easily find their way into the house and the family’s private life is well hidden from the passers-by’s eyes.</p>\r\n<p>The heart and the main space of the house is an open terrace facing the south which is surrounded by all the other rooms. Due to the complete glazing of this façade, there is a picturesque view of the landscape from the whole house and each room is filled with the nature’s atmosphere. Dense curtains are installed to easily confine the spaces and protect them from a too intensive sunlight.</p>\r\n<p>The first floor is a zone of open spaces that almost flows into each other. The first floor’s space is designed just like the street so that you can walk down the hallway fast and easily with no borders or physical obstacles. Just like in the city streets, each corner of the room opens up to different spaces – a square, walls or a little yard, which allows you to divide the functional zones without walls or doors. The ground floor has a living room, TV zone, kitchen, guest’s room, children’s room and the entrance to the garage.</p>\r\n<p>The first floor is all about the adult zone – a separate small world where all the spaces are designed around their Japanese patio style. The bedroom, the dressing, the home office and the bathroom are located on this floor. Unlike the ground floor, the first one is more closed and intimate. It allows the owners to relax and work in peace. The two dimensional space of the hallway, there are windows which not only give the additional light but also allows the parents to watch over their children from upstairs.</p>\r\n<p>The interior’s design is modern and involves a calm color scheme, usage of ecological materials and comfortable furniture. Rooms are not overloaded with a large number of small details and décor elements. The finishing feature was the “honesty” of the design, as most walls have been left in their construction stage and material – concrete. In contrast with such rough walls, pieces of modern design and chandeliers look just great. The interior of the house consists of the necessary minimum: contrasts and calmness, severity and a touch of luxury.</p>', 'Villa', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'villa__trashed', '', '', '2017-06-21 15:03:28', '2017-06-21 13:03:28', '', 0, 'https://space-filling.codetiburon.com/?post_type=sf_portfolio&#038;p=677', 0, 'sf_portfolio', '', 0),
